union closed set system.definition_text: A set system $\F$ is \emph{union closed} if for all $A,B \in \F$ we have $A \cup B \in \F$

c-approximate union closed set system.definition_text: A set system $\F$ is $c$-approximate union closed if for at least a $c$-fraction of the pairs $A,B \in \F$ we have $A \cup B \in \F$.

psi.definition_text: Gilmer conjectured that his technique can be sharpened to give the constant $\psi := \frac{3-\sqrt{5}}{2} \approx 0.38$. Below we verify his conjecture, and also show that it is optimal for ``approximate'' union closed set systems.

varphi.definition_text: Let \varphi = 1-\psi =\frac{\sqrt{5}-1}{2} be the positive root of x^2+x-1=0.

c-approximate union closed.definition_text: A set system $\F$ is $c$-approximate union closed if for at least a $c$-fraction of the pairs $A,B \in \F$ we have $A \cup B \in \F$.

set system.definition_text: A set system is called union closed if for any two sets in the set system their union is also in the set system.
